textasciicircum}\{-1\}\$ in the MMT data set, but further observations are required to verify this. The flattened metal-rich population invalidates assumptions built into simple dynamical mass estimators, so we computed new astrophysical dark matter annihilation (J) and decay profiles based on the rounder, hotter metal-poor population and inferred \${\textbackslash}log \_\{10\}\{(J(0\{{\textasciicircum}\{{\textbackslash}circ\}\_\{.\}\}5)/\{{\textbackslash}rm GeV{\textasciicircum}\{2\} {\textbackslash}, cm{\textasciicircum}\{-5\}\})\}{\textbackslash}approx 19.1\$ for the Keck data set. Our results paint a more complex picture of the evolution of UMi than previously discussed.},
